<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 2000 4000 and 8000 MODELS BUILT OCTOBER 1, 1998 AND AFTER -
        SPEEDOMETER/TACHOMETER, GAUGES AND WARNING LIGHTS - 9800 - Troubleshooting - ENGINE EXHAUST TEMPERATURE
        (PYROMETER)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>ENGINE EXHAUST TEMPERATURE (PYROMETER)</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s08245x_8.xml" xrefid="x0824510">Pyrometer
                    <xref refid="x0824510"/>
                </hotlnk>
                for an operation description of the pyrometer system.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Pyrometer Reads Full Scale With Key ON</title>
            <para>If the circuits to the pyrometer control module have an open circuit (thermocouple burns out for
                example), the control module produces a full scale signal to the gauge.
            </para>
            <table id="t0824510">
                <title>Pyrometer Reads Full Scale With Key ON</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.54in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.96in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.71in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" colwidth="1.21in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES- IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect thermocouple leads at connector (591). Measure resistance to ground at
                                    the 18 gauge red, and then the yellow wires.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(591), 18 gauge red and then the yellow wires to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Reconnect (591). Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the thermocouple/lead assembly.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Disconnect thermocouple leads from pyrometer control module at connector (592).
                                    Measure resistance to ground at the 18 gauge red, and then the yellow wires.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(592), 18 gauge red and then the yellow wires to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Replace the thermocouple/lead assembly between connector (592) and (591).</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (592), measure the resistance between the red and yellow wires in the
                                    thermocouple assembly.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(592), red and yellow wires.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>3 to 4 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the pyrometer control module.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Reconnect (592). Replace the thermocouple assembly.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Pyrometer Reads Low or No Exhaust Temperature</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s08245x_8.xml" xrefid="x0824510">Pyrometer
                    <xref refid="x0824510"/>
                </hotlnk>
                for an operation description of the pyrometer system.
            </para>
            <para>Fuse locations vary; check inside power distribution center for actual location.</para>
            <table id="t0824511">
                <title>Pyrometer Reads Low or No Exhaust Temperature</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.54in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.96in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.71in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" colwidth="1.24in"/>
                    <spanspec namest="1" nameend="7" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES- IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Check 10A fuse F10-A* for open condition.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>F10-A*</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then replace fuse.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Disconnect connector (42). At (42) measure voltage to ground at circuit 25.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(42), 25 to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>12&#177;1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 25, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>At connector (42) measure voltage between circuits 25 and 11-GAB.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(42), 25 and 11- GAB.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>12&#177;1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate open in circuit 11-GAB, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Remove connector (73) from gauge cluster, and at (73) measure resistance to ground
                                    at circuit 25A.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(73), 25A to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate short to ground in circuit 25A, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>At connector (42), use a test lead to jumper circuit 25A to ground. At connector
                                    (73) measure resistance to ground at circuit 25A.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(73), 25A to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Remove jumper and go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 25A, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Measure resistance at connector (73) circuit 25B to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(73), 25B to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate short to ground in circuit 25B, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>7.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>At connector (42), use a test lead to jumper circuit 25B to ground. At connector
                                    (73) measure resistance to ground at circuit 25B.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(73), 25B to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Remove jumper, reconnect (42) and go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 25B, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>8.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>At connector (73) measure resistance to ground at circuit 11-GV.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(73), 11-GV to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 11-GV/11-GF, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>9.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Measure voltage to ground at connector (73) circuit 25A.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(73), 25A to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>7.7 to 8.7 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Replace control module.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>10.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Remove pyrometer gauge. Measure resistance between cluster connector (73) cavity
                                    2, and the pyrometer ground pin
                                    <hotlnk document="s08245x_27.xml" xrefid="f0824518">(Figure 18)</hotlnk>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(73), cavity 2, and ground pin.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Open in cluster circuit. Replace the gauge cluster.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>11.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Measure resistance between cluster connector (73) cavity 3 and the pyrometer
                                    accessory pin
                                    <hotlnk document="s08245x_27.xml" xrefid="f0824518">(Figure 18)</hotlnk>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(73), cavity 3, and accessory pin.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Open in cluster circuit. Replace the gauge cluster.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>12.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>With gauge tester still connected, set to 88 ohms. Does fuel gauge read full?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(73), cavity 16, and ignition pin.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Replace gauge and go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Open in cluster circuit. Replace the gauge cluster.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>13.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Run engine to generate exhaust temperature. Use thermometer to measure. Measure
                                    voltage to ground at connector (73) circuit 25B.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(73), 25B to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>600&#176;F (315.6&#176;C) = 1.75 volts, 1200&#176;F (649&#176;C) = 4.83 volts.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Circuit and gauge test good. Reconnect (73).</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Replace the pyrometer control module.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="7" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">* Fuse locations vary; check inside power distribution center for
                                        actual location.
                                    </emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
